It will of course be shipped on just about every new computer on sale from October 26 and dealers will not offer or be able to offer new computers with a previous OS. This is normal Microsoft procedure, and any dealer offering or selling boxes with W7 or earlier are liable to lose their license to sell MS machines.
Short of persuading a dealer to sell a computer without an OS or buying a Mac people will be stuck with that OS.

Windows 8 hardware will come with the Secure Boot technology enabled in the Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI), meaning that only operating systems with an appropriate digital signature will be able to boot.

So what of Tails? Is the next version being prepared to deal with this?
